node.text: Videos showing people smuggling migrants past Border Patrol checkpoints and flashing thousands of dollars in cash are being posted on TikTok, Texas State Troopers say. This is a new and dangerous tactic to recruit teens to drive migrants from the US-Mexico border to Houston and other Texas cities — with one video offering $4,500 per person they smuggle. CNN's @rosaflorescnn reports.

node.text: Ashley Diamond, a transgender woman, has spent the last decade in and out of men's prisons in Georgia. Now, she's suing the Georgia Department of Corrections to be transferred to a women's facility. ​

⁠

node.text:
Here's some good news as you pour another cup of coffee: Drinking up to three cups of coffee a day may protect your heart, a new study finds. Regular coffee consumption was associated with a decreased risk of death from heart disease, stroke and early death from any cause when compared to non-coffee drinkers.⁠
⁠
(📸: Shutterstock)⁠

node.text:
The last US military planes have left Afghanistan, Commander of US Central Command Gen. Frank McKenzie announced Monday. The departure marks the end of a fraught, chaotic and bloody exit from the United States’ longest war.⁠
⁠
(📸: Aamir Qureshi/AFP/Getty Images)⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 30, 2021. May be an illustration of 1 person.

node.text:
A young Afghan artist created this haunting image of her homeland's fall to the Taliban. Sara Rahmani, who moved from Kabul to the US four years ago, made a drawing showing both the beauty and desperation in Afghanistan.⁠
⁠
"This is the portrait of the girl that I started, and it really turned sad," she said. "You see the good side, when she has a splinter of light — it's all about the good side of my Afghanistan before the Taliban took over our country."⁠
⁠
(📸: @sara_official_artgallery/Instagram)

node.text: Covid-19 cases in the US have surged in recent weeks, as the highly infectious Delta variant spreads among unvaccinated Americans. Nationally, 52.1% of the population was fully vaccinated as of Saturday, according to data from the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention.⁠

The European Union recommended on Monday that Americans should be banned from nonessential travel to the 27 nations in the EU, which includes France, Italy, and Germany.⁠
⁠

node.text:
It's been one year since Jacob Blake was shot seven times by a Kenosha police officer who was responding to a call for a domestic incident. Blake told CNN he's cynical about the progress made in policing and his community — and about hatred in general during the past year in the aftermath of his own shooting and the killings of Breonna Taylor and George Floyd. ⁠
⁠
Tap the link in our bio to read the exclusive interview with @omarcnn.

node.text:
Hurricane Ida ripped across southeastern Louisiana, killing at least one person, obliterating roofs, sapping power and sending rescuers scrambling Monday morning. Ida, now a slow-moving tropical storm over southwestern Mississippi, still will pose a major threat for more flooding not just in those two states but also into the Tennessee and Ohio valleys as it crawls north over the next few days.

(📸: Scott Olson/Getty Images, Mark Felix/AFP/Getty Images, Gerald Herbert/AP, Luke Sharrett/Bloomberg/Getty Images, Thomas Pesquet/ESA/NASA, Brandon Bell/Getty Images and Patrick T. Fallon/AFP)
